cmmbqdu2001onb2itkrq165h8	Between the Buried and Me	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	\N	{}	Resound Presents: Between The Buried And Me w/ Imperial Triumphant, & Fallujah in Austin, TX at Mohawk (outdoor) on Wednesday, June 10, 2026 . Progressive metal visionaries Between the Buried and Me return with their most immersive and eclectic record yet-The Blue Nowhere, their first on InsideOutMusic. Mixing uncharted musical detours with their distinctive aggressive identity, the band create a conceptual world unlike anything in their incredible catalog, inviting the listener to experience the journey on their own terms. Though the story takes place in a hotel-The Blue Nowhere-don&rsquo;t expect haunted corridors or shadowy figures behind every door. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s more of a feeling-those moments when you feel alone in the world and use that solitude to reflect on the human experience,&rdquo; Rogers clarifies. &ldquo;It exists in a space where no one can find you, hidden from all forms of reality-that&rsquo;s The Blue Nowhere.&rdquo; Trying something new is not unusual for the group, who once again find ways to expand their musical palette while maintaining the band&rsquo;s core sound. No more surprising is the album opener, &ldquo;Things We Tell Ourselves in the Dark,&rdquo; which sets the tone with INXS and Duran Duran-inspired textures, even incorporating 90125-era Yes, filtered through BTBAM&rsquo;s signature chaos. Meanwhile, &ldquo;Absent Thereafter&rdquo; is a quintessential BTBAM track-layered, intense, and unrelentingly dynamic, this 10+ minute opus delivers everything a BTBAM fan could want and more. Between the Buried and Me remain allergic to stagnation, and The Blue Nowhere proves their creative drive is stronger than ever. &ldquo;It feels like a natural evolution for the band,&rdquo; says Rogers. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re not repeating ourselves. We&rsquo;re lucky to have a fanbase that&rsquo;s along for the ride. | Imperial Triumphant, Fallujah	\N	\N	2026-03-04 07:44:24.9