cmmbpbcml00crb2it48n02sdw	cmmbpbcm300cob2it2kcviorv	\N	Finally! But not the end by a long shot. I had the privilege to record with my brosky, Brannen Temple. I've known of Brannen Temple since he was about 16 years young. Early on I managed to catch him smashing drums with all the finesse and facility of a well-rounded pro, speaking the language of drums very well and quite effortlessly. BTemp has quite an impressive career, having played with some of the most celebrated artists of our day, including Janet Jackson, Rose McGowan, Fastball, Monte Montgomery, Sheena Easton, Kevin Paige, Jimmie Vaughan, Dixie Chicks, Lee Roy Parnell, Jody Watley, Patrice Rushen, and Chaka Khan, and more recently Eric Johnson, Eric Burdon, Ruthie Foster, and Gary Clark Jr. Temple is also the recipient of 3 Grammy awards. The coolest thing is he's a true brother and friend.\n\n#toddefunk #officialtoddefunk #brannentemple #btempdrums #atxmusic #austinmusic #austinmusicscene #arlynstudios #drummer\n#drums #funkydrummer #bassplayers #bassguitar #austinlivemusic	2025-11-14 00:26:17	\N	2026-03-04 07:14:29.421	\N
