cmmbprju700neb2it8gg8qn7l	cmmbprjts00nbb2it8wq7x82h	\N	Our second record “They Promised Us Heaven” is up for preorder today through @deadbrokerekerds in the US and @shieldrecordingsnl in the EU and should be shipping around the end of September. We’re really proud of this one and hope you’ll pick up a copy. Mike at Dead Broke says it’s “Smart & Melodic social-political punk from Texas. Members of Low Culture, Shang-A-Lang, Nocturnal Prose and more. Their sophomore album and hands down best batch of songs to date.” 100 on red vinyl and the rest are on black. \n\nYou can also hear a new song from the record called “Worse Than Any Bomb” on Bandcamp or wherever you stream music (minus Spotify). This song is about how powerful institutions tend do whatever they can to stifle speech. It’s about how, in their world, illuminating a genocide is worse than committing one; demanding the end of killing is worse than the killing itself. While the current president of the United States has detained and deported people for daring saying “Free Palestine,” this song was written over a year ago, when a different old white man held the reins of power. He, was also calling anti-war protesters antisemitic and clamoring for their arrest. The song was written while thinking about him licking an ice cream cone and talking about a “ceasefire” that still hasn’t come. \n\n#deadbrokerekerds #shieldrecordings	2025-08-22 21:08:00	\N	2026-03-04 07:27:05.263	\N
