cmmbq769b014zb2itriy30xyn	cmmbq768r014tb2itu6yeuy3r	\N	Raising a glass, or perhaps a brownie is more fitting, to my wonderful Grandma, Janice Loyce Bertman who passed away over the holidays. She was the sweetest and coolest and I feel so lucky to have had her in my life for so long. \nMy sister Jennifer and I regularly reference little things she would say or do, her laugh and the joy she gave to all of us. We are eternally grateful for the Grandma impact. \nShe loved cooking and shopping and being with her family. She could knit with the best of them. She would spend countless hours creating something beautiful just to give it away. \nJennifer has mastered her baked squash recipe. And for years our Mom has taken to several other grandma classic dishes. I’m still working on this and overdue for another attempt. \nI love the kindness she showed to my Dad who was always ready to single handedly start on a new home improvement project for her. She spent 98 years spreading joy. She had a special bond with all of us, especially my Mom. ❤️	2026-02-02 00:16:39	\N	2026-03-04 07:39:14.159	\N
